This is ill informed. Burns do fail. It's not '0 failure' by any means. Dragon Fear is low resist, has longer range than MB, and interrupts all casting. They don't roar all the time but if they do at the right time, you have a good chance for a wipe. 1 feared burner and one of the others could crit. 2+ and it's over. And you have over two hours till you can do it again, which means basically you will not have a second chance.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Ohh and the only time MB really, REALLY hurts mid teir guilds is you can have your people there and buffing for a dragon when suddenly 5-6 MB wizzies run in, MB the mob dead and port out, 6 people are much much faster then 20-30  - Seaten<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes. This would be bad. If it happenned. It hasn't happenned on my server. I don't know for sure but I suspect it doesn't on most.<br>
